Sequel to the retirement of the former Registrar, Dr M. S. Ayeerun, on May 12, the Governing Council of Adekunle Ajasin University Akungba Akoko (AAUA), has appointed Mr. Opeoluwa Akinfemiwa as the Acting Registrar, with effect from May, 13, 2019. Akinfemiwa hails from Ile Oluji in Ondo State and has a B.A. honours degree in History and Archeology from the University of Ibadan as well as a Master’s Degree in Public Administration from Lagos State University, Ojo. Until his appointment, he was the Deputy Registrar (Academic Affairs) in the University.